  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Study Window
  author: Eo Segyeom
  language: eng
  text: |-
    I caught a verse and wrote it in my study window—
    when paper tears, the poem tears too.
    Good poetry people will surely pass on,
    bad poetry people will surely spit upon.
    If people transmit it, what harm is a tear?
    If people spit on it, a tear is welcome.
    I laugh once, mount my horse, and ride home—
    a thousand years hence, only poetry will know me.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'study window' (書窓) serves as both the literal place of composition and a metaphor for the poet's modest circumstances and humble artistic practice.
  - key: ''
    value: The tension between the poem's material fragility and its potential spiritual permanence reflects classical Chinese and Korean poetic philosophy about art's enduring value beyond physical form.
